Coloration: Head and body with dark brown mottling in live individuals. Several dark bars radiate from orbitals. Dark stripes on each side of body. A shiny, greenish blotch on upper side of operculum. A large dark blotch on base of caudal fin. Dorsal fins, anal fin and caudal fin mottled (
Figure 2
). Preserved specimens light brown, with stripes and irregular darker blotches on each side of body. Abdominal pale, slightly yellowish (
Figure 3
).
